# System admin authorization

## Scope

Routes under `/system/*` are **platform** administration for users with the backend `system_admin` role. They are separate from event-scoped pages under `/` (schedule, sessions, settings, etc.).

## Verification (required)

- Authorization is proven only by **`GET /admin/ping`** with the Bearer token from `useUserStore`.
- Treat access as granted only when the response body has **`data.ok === true`** (see `controllers.AdminPingResponse` in [docs/rest_api/swagger.json](docs/rest_api/swagger.json)).
- **401** → unauthenticated (redirect to `/login`).
- **403** or any other failure → deny (fail closed; redirect `/`).

## Route guard

- All system admin pages must live under the `/system` route branch in [src/routes/index.tsx](src/routes/index.tsx), wrapped by **`RequireAuth` → `RequireSystemAdmin` → `SystemAdminLayout`** (not `AppLayout`).
- Use [SystemAdminLayout](src/components/SystemAdminLayout.tsx) for platform UI: dedicated sidebar, no event selector. Add nav items in `systemNavMain` there, not in `AppLayout`.
- Never add platform-admin pages as children of the unguarded `/` tree.
- Do not duplicate `RequireSystemAdmin` on every child route unless introducing a nested layout that needs its own guard boundary.

## Hooks and cache

- Use **`useAdminPing()`** and **`queryKeys.admin.ping`** for the ping query.
- Do **not** persist “is system admin” in Zustand, localStorage, or JWT-derived flags.
- Ping query: `staleTime: 0`, `refetchOnMount: "always"`, no retry on 401/403.
- New `/admin/*` API hooks: types from swagger, keys under `queryKeys.admin.*`, `apiClient` in `src/hooks/`. Server still enforces role on every call.

## Forbidden

- Do **not** gate routes or UI on `user.role`, JWT `roles`, or client-only checks.
- Do **not** skip the route guard because the sidebar hides the System link (nav is UX only).
- Do **not** assume login success implies system admin access.

## Fail closed

On ping error, non-ok body, 403, or network failure after retries: deny access (redirect `/`). On 401: redirect `/login`.
